<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07928</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING THE ESTABLISHMENT OF COMPUTER LABORATORY IN ALL PUBLIC ELEMENTARY AND SECONDARY SCHOOLS AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to give priority to promote the use of computer technology and literacy in basic education, especially in public schools;
Seeks to enhance and facilitate learning and education of pupils and students and provide access to computers and the Internet by both learners and teachers; Provides that every public elementary and high school students in the country shall have at least one (1) room that shall be used as computer laboratory.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Computer and Internet Literacy for Public School Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>OLIVAREZ, ERIC L.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-08-08)</td><td>2. Suansing (E.) (000 2018-09-18)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>